author: @DMC1982
text:
UN experts demand justice for Al Jazeera journalist on one year anniversary of her killing.
GENEVA (11 May 2023)  On the one-year anniversary of Shireen Abu Akleh killing, UN experts raised the alarm today that justice for the journalist death has been denied.
fter a year, Israeli authorities have failed to hold the perpetrators of Abu Akleh killing accountable, while independent investigations have pointed at the culpability of Israeli forces. Justice remains, again, hostage of politics, the experts said.
Shireen Abu Akleh, a Palestinian-American journalist and acclaimed correspondent for Al Jazeera, was shot dead on 11 May 2022, while performing her duty as a journalist reporting on Israel raid in the Jenin refugee camp. Several independent investigations carried out by various bodies and organisations, including the Office of the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights, concluded that Abu Akleh was most likely killed by seemingly well-targeted shots fired by Israeli forces, despite her wearing clear identification as a journalist. Internal investigations carried out by the Israeli Defence Force (IDF) found  high possibility that Abu Akleh was ccidentally hit by IDF gunfire. However, to date, Israeli authorities have not opened a criminal investigation into her death or held anyone accountable.
o far, every one of the requirements under international law for the investigation of potentially unlawful deaths, namely promptness, effectiveness and thoroughness, independence and impartiality and transparency, appears to have been violated in this case, the experts said.
nternational law demands, at minimum an effective, thorough, independent, impartial and transparent investigation into Abu Akleh death. These steps must be carried out in accordance with applicable international standards, including theMinnesota Protocol on the Investigation of Potentially Unlawful Death (2016). Failing to carry out a prompt and effective investigation, followed by prosecution and judicial process, may in itself constitute a violation of the right to life, they said.
e also urge the Israeli authorities to ensure that those responsible are held accountable without delay, the experts said, recalling that Ms. Abu Akleh family must have access to justice, truth and adequate reparation, and emphasising that the whole world needs to know what happened.
he safety of journalists, particularly in situations of conflict and occupation, is critical to support accountability and transparency, the experts said. he deliberate killing of a journalist in such situations amounts
to extrajudicial execution, an egregious violation of the right to life, and wilful killing under the fourth Geneva Convention. It is thus paramount that journalists are provided with effective protective measures.
The experts also decried the record-high number of killings of Palestinians in the occupied West Bank and East Jerusalem in recent months in the context of raids by Israeli forces, often targeting refugee camps. In 2022, out of 9000 Israeli operations, 704 targeted refugee camps in the occupied West Bank. In 2023, already more than 7000 Palestinians have been killed more than 20000 injured in the context of such operations, including in Jenin, Nablus, Jericho and Gaza.Since 2001, at least 21 Palestinian journalists have been reportedly killed by the IDF in the occupied Palestinian territory and no one has been held accountable for those deaths.
vidence indicates that the Israeli forces repeatedly deploy lethal force against Palestinians in violation of international law, which prohibits intentional lethal use of firearms except when strictly unavoidable to protect life, the experts said.
he killing of Shireen Abu Akleh is symbolic, embodying grave human rights violations that Palestinians have faced under the Israeli occupation for over 55 years, the experts said. heir rights to self-determination, life, freedom of expression have been consistently violated. The Palestinian people live under the yoke of pervasive impunity and lack of reparations for violations committed, they said.
The experts urged the international community to take concrete action in the face of these violations. he United Nations Charter is betrayed every day in the occupied Palestinian territory, they said. 
The expertsraisedthe matter with the Israeli Government and dulycalledfor a prompt, transparent, thorough and independent investigation into Abu Akleh death, for which they also offered their specialised forensic assistance and technical advice. The Israeli Government has not responded to the communication to date.

text:
MPORTANT FACTS ABOUT PALESTINE 
Dear Respected All,Peace and Blessings. 

Palestine The Truth Must Be Known (Synopsis) 

In 1896, an enlightened White Austro-Hungarian European Zionist, Theodore Herzle, conceived a brazen political vision for Jews to have a separate national home in Palestine. Twenty-one years later, this cynical ideology and sinister agenda to transfer world Jewry into Palestine gained momentum and led to the presumptuous Balfour Declaration of 1917 in which the British connived and promised  national home for the Jewish people in Palestine. Both treacherous schemes were hatched without consulting the indigenous Palestinian people, vehemently against their popular democratic will and contrary to their right to national independence and self-determination as a distinct sovereign people. 

The stage has been set and the Zionist master plan was expeditiously put into motion. By the mid-1930s tens of thousands of foreign Jews forcibly entered Palestine thus provoking a failed Arab Revolt. This mass illegal influx of European Jews further heightened later in the early 1940s under the British Mandate, following the Holocaust in Germany. 

Some thirty years thereafter or just over half a century from inception, at the world stage, conspiracies against the Palestinian people took on a more insidious and repugnant reality. On November 29, 1947 in a dramatic move, the UN unilaterally determined that Palestine must be taken from its indigenous population and awarded to alien White European Zionist Jewish refugees. Again, as in the fateful years of 1896 and 1917, the contrived UN Partition Plan was hastily adopted without consulting the indigenous Palestinian people themselves, in utter contempt, lack of respect for their right to self-determination and the complete disregard for the national independence, the territorial sovereignty and integrity of their country. 

More decisively as facts on the ground unfortunately unfolded rapidly, the ambitions European Jews then unleashed the monstrous Plan Dalet and the shock and horror began in Palestine! At great speed, the dreadful Nakba emerged as Zionist mercenaries forcefully usurped the land, confiscated private property, killed thousands (even animals) and drove hundreds of thousands of Palestinians from their own country as displaced and beleaguered refugees.Indeed, heavily supported by the self-righteous West, the embryonic Zionist Apartheid entity boastfully declared itself on May 15, 1948, through a brutal military campaign perpetrated by three well-known Zionist terrorist groups the Stern Gang, the Haganah and Irgun. 

Ever since, these very terrorists became an integral part of the seminal Zionist Apartheid regime and its IDF, both of which together in unison continue with gross impunity to occupy, oppress, terrorize and commit genocide against the indigenous Palestinian population struggling for their freedom.
Again, this injustice with the full, unhinged, sustained and unconditional political, financial and military support of the civilized democratic West, led primarily by the United States and its staunch allies. 

For well over 75 hopeless years of blatant injustice, Zionist propaganda machine was busy flooding the world consciousness with blatant lies and heinous deception in order to achieve their malign goals. Plagued by cruel, illegal and inhumane Zionist Apartheid occupation and genocide in Palestine, the disenfranchised Palestinian people reserve the legitimate, legal and moral right and are indeed compelled to fight for the liberation of their homeland by any and every means possible. 

Palestinians are NOT 'terrorists'! Despite the enormous political, economic and military challenges, constraints and struggles they are enduring, they are legitimate, admirable and determined freedom fighters and heroes, deserving of full respect, encouragement and every support necessary for their ultimate victory. 

Indeed, the passive international community likewise has a binding, legitimate, legal and moral obligation to stop the bold Zionist Apartheid crimes, atrocities, disenfranchisement, military occupation, ethnic cleansing, economic strangulation and genocide against the indigenous Palestinian people, commited every day before our eyes. 

The sad reality is that after 75 grueling years of the unabated recalcitrance of Zionist Apartheid occupation and genocide, nothing really meaningful has been done to seriously address the Palestinian issue justly by world leaders, including the very UN, which played a decisive role in institutionally augmenting the problem in the first place, instead of averting it completely. Indeed, the United States and its close allies in their malign agenda and ulterior motives, callously continue to openly block and obstruct any progress for peace, regional stability and justice on the Palestine Question. 

It is time for Justice! Palestine must be completely liberated from Zionist Apartheid brutalization, occupation and genocide. The Palestinian people are entitled to enjoy the same basic rights, fundamental freedoms, democracy and dignity that every human being deserves. The world can no longer sit and wait idly by, in silence or indifference. It's now time to act decisively, not merely because it is a collective responsibility, but truly as a high moral duty to defend the truth and justice and achieve a durable and lasting peace on this most vexing and enduring issue of Palestine entrusted upon mankind. One way or another, Palestinian victory is inevitable! 

Thank you. 

Dr. Mobarak Ali

We, the American Indian Empowerment PAC, hereby issue this Cease and Desist notice to all legal, elected, appointed, juristic, citizens, residents, resident aliens, for-profit and non-profit corporate persons, and all other non-governmental organizations under the jurisdiction of the United States.

It has come to our attention that individuals, organizations, and corporations are deliberately misclassifying Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent as nderserved arginalized inorities ommunities of color  "Black" or "African American" for profit. This misclassification violates treaties, constitutions, and covenants, and it is imperative that this practice be discontinued immediately.

Misidentifying Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent as "Black" or "African American" erases their unique cultural heritage and history, infringing upon their right to self-determination and self-identification. The Indian Bill of Rights, Indian Civil Rights Act, and American Indian Self-determination and Education Assistance Act of 1975 were enacted to protect the rights of American Indians and colonial European descent Americans. Furthermore, treaties such as the Treaty of Dancing Rabbit Creek, the Treaty with the Cherokee, and the Treaty of Delaware were established to safeguard the sovereignty and self-determination of American Indian tribes. The Bill of Rights and the Constitution of the United States also ensure the fundamental rights of all Americans, regardless of their race or ethnicity. Additionally, the United Nations Declaration of the Rights of Indigenous Peoples recognizes the right of Indigenous peoples to self-determination and the preservation of their cultural identity.

By perpetuating the false belief in race and imposing the identity of "Black" or "African American" on Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent, these individuals, organizations, and corporations are promoting a caste system identity that does not exist and undermining the principles of liberty and justice for all upon which the United States of America was founded.

Therefore, we demand that all social media companies, elected officials, public servants, public corporations, and their agents and partners immediately cease and desist from using terms such as FBA, Black, Afro-American, African Americans, minorities, people of color, communities of color, ADOS, or any other marketing slogan or racist term to describe and determine the identity of Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent with ruddy, tawny, brunette, fair, swarthy, and dark skin tones as "Black" or "African American."

Failure to comply with this Cease and Desist notice will result in legal action to protect the rights and identities of Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent.

This notice is issued under the authority of PUBLIC LAW 93-638, Indian Civil Rights Act of 1968 (ICRA), 25 U.S.C. 1301-1304 (ICRA).

text:
History of Ottoman - 13

    Jews in Ottoman

       Among the few inhabitants of Constantinople ( after victory of Constantinople in 1453 by Mehmet-II, Ottoman Sultan)  to have survived the Turkish seizure of the city were the Jews of the Balat quarter. Not long after the appointment of Gennadius ( the priest, first patriarch of Orthodox welcomed by Mehmed, after fall of Constantinople in 1453 ) or perhaps at the same time, Mehmed also selected a chief rabbi to preside over all the Jewish congregations of Turkey. His choice fell on Moshe Capsali, a man of piety and learning, founder of a celebrated family of scholars Elijah Capsali, who in the sixteenth century wrote a Hebrew history of the Ottoman Empire that is still awaiting publication, may have been descended from him. The sultan, we are told, even made him a member of the imperial council (divan) , where he was honored by a seat next to the mufti, thus gaining precedence over the Greek patriarch furthermore, he delegated to Capali certain political powers over the Jewish congregations of Turkey. It was Moshe Capsali who assigned the taxes to be paid individually or collectively by the Jews, appointed officials to collect them, and transmitted 
 the proceeds to the sultan's treasury. He also possessed penal authority over all members of the Jewish community and the right to confirm the appointment of rabbis. In a word, he was the head and official representative of the Jewish community in the Ottoman Empire. 
             Under the Conqueror, if the accounts of Jewish contemporaries are to be believed, Turkey was a paradise for the Jews, who were cruelly oppressed in Western Europe. Jewish emigrants from Germany were overjoyed at the favored position of the Jews in Turkey. They were free to 
live and trade as they pleased. There was no "golden penny" to pay, no crown taxes amounting to a third of their fortune. They could dispose freely of their property and dress as they saw fit, in silk and satin if they wished. Their enterprise found rich sources of profit, though it is true that they were soon obliged to limit their activities to commerce and moneylending. In 1454 Isaac Sarfati, a Jew born in Germany of French descent, sent a circular letter to the Jews of the Rhineland, Swabia, Styria, Moravia, and Hungary in which he spoke with enthusiasm of the fortunate conditions of the Jews under the Crescent in contrast to their yoke under the Cross, and encouraged his coreligionaries to leave the "great torture chamber" and come to Turkey. The years that followed witnessed a massive emigration of Jews to the Turkish paradise, especially from Germany. Certain countries, Italy in particular, prevented their Jews from leaving."

      "  There can be no doubt about Mehmed's religious tolerance. If even a part of what Isaac Sarfati wrote from Turkey in his circular letter of 1454 to the Jews of Central Europe about the favorable situation of his coreligionaries under the Crescent was true, Mehmed's empire must have been a paradise for non-Moslem subjects (reaya) , especially Jews. Turkey, Sarfati wrote, was a country where nothing was lacking. Every man could spend his life unmolested under his fig tree and his vine. In judging this letter with its invitation to emigrate to the Ottoman Empire, we must not, of course, forget that the situation of the Jews in Central Europe in the middle of the fifteenth century was particularly wretched, that they were subject to incessant persecution, and that measured by these condiions, Turkey, where no one was molested for his faith, could promise a truly blissful life. It must also be borne in mind that in his commercial undertakings and his fiscal policy, Mehmed preferred to rely on the help of Jews, including his physician Maestro lacopo, whom he sometimes, to the dissatisfaction of the Moslems, employed as his financial adviser. But also in Christian quarters, as it is more than once confirmed, each man could "seek salvation in his own way," complete religious freedom prevailed, and no one incurred serious difficulties because of his faith. There can be no doubt that the Christian inhabitants of places far from the seat of government were often oppressed and unjustly treated, but it is equally certain that this was not the work of the supreme authorities. The truly magnanimous treatment of non-Moslems in the Ottoman Empire under Mehmed can in large measure be attributed to his indulgence and mildness in religious matters, qualities which were in all likelihood closely related to his own liberal ideas on religion."

Book Mehmed the

We, the American Indian Empowerment PAC, hereby issue this Cease and Desist notice to all legal, elected, appointed, juristic, citizens, residents, resident aliens, for-profit and non-profit corporate persons, and all other non-governmental organizations under the jurisdiction of the United States.

It has come to our attention that individuals, organizations, and corporations are deliberately misclassifying Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent as "Black" or "African American" for profit. This misclassification violates treaties, constitutions, and covenants, and it is imperative that this practice be discontinued immediately.

Misidentifying Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent as "Black" or "African American" erases their unique cultural heritage and history, infringing upon their right to self-determination and self-identification. The Indian Bill of Rights, Indian Civil Rights Act, and American Indian Self-determination and Education Assistance Act of 1975 were enacted to protect the rights of American Indians and colonial European descent Americans. Furthermore, treaties such as the Treaty of Dancing Rabbit Creek, the Treaty with the Cherokee, and the Treaty of Delaware were established to safeguard the sovereignty and self-determination of American Indian tribes. The Bill of Rights and the Constitution of the United States also ensure the fundamental rights of all Americans, regardless of their race or ethnicity. Additionally, the United Nations Declaration of the Rights of Indigenous Peoples recognizes the right of Indigenous peoples to self-determination and the preservation of their cultural identity.

By perpetuating the false belief in race and imposing the identity of "Black" or "African American" on Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent, these individuals, organizations, and corporations are promoting a caste system identity that does not exist and undermining the principles of liberty and justice for all upon which the United States of America was founded.

Therefore, we demand that all social media companies, elected officials, public servants, public corporations, and their agents and partners immediately cease and desist from using terms such as FBA, Black, Afro-American, African Americans, minorities, people of color, communities of color, ADOS, or any other marketing slogan or racist term to describe and determine the identity of Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent with ruddy, tawny, brunette, fair, swarthy, and dark skin tones as "Black" or "African American."

Failure to comply with this Cease and Desist notice will result in legal action to protect the rights and identities of Americans of American Indian and colonial European descent.

This notice is issued under the authority of PUBLIC LAW 93-638, Indian Civil Rights Act of 1968 (ICRA), 25 U.S.C. 1301-1304 (ICRA).

Sincerely,
American Indian Empowerment PAC

author: @Poppy-zm2yh
text:
salRL-eb3zc can we stop with this bullshit? Israel has never given one free thing to palestinians. Water? You mean the water that belongs to the west bank, so to Palestine, that they FORBID palestinians to use? They deny access to water courses, they deny permitts to build wells, they even destroy rain water cisterns on palestinian land. Because of this around 180 palestinian communities in the west bank don't have access to running water, even if they are connected to the water network, no water comes through it. 
Meanwhile Mekorot, an israeli state-owned company, built a water network, tapped water springs and sunk wells to service israel and the settlers in the west bank. They sell water to Palestinians only in restricted amounts decided by Israel, and for prices that range between 4 and 10 dollars for cubic liter (which to give you some perspective in my first world country would costs around 60 cents), so for many poor families the cost of water amounts to half their monthly earning. 
So while palestinians struggle to survive, settlers can enjoy their pools and irrigate their fields as much as they want, even just a few hundred meters away.
According to the WHO, the water consumption (drinking, cooking and hygiene) of a person should be around 100 liters per day. An sraeli settler consumes around 300 liters per day, but some west bank palestinian communities have access to as little as 20 liters per day per person. 

Electricity? Still not given for free. What the Israel Electric Corporation provides (still in very restricted amounts) to Gaza, is fully paid by the taxes collected by the Palestinian Authority. In the west bank, while they are running on debt, it's still definetly not donated in any capacity, and  the debt is expected to be payed back.
And I'm sure that if Israel fucked off from the occupied territories, they would enjoy producing their own energy (something they are already working towards) or buying from other nations. 

Jobs? Oh, my! So charitable, aren't they? They allow palestinians to work for them for cheap after having to go through hours of check points. We should give them a humanitarian prize. 
You know in the Jim Crow US, Black people were allowed to have jobs, right? Where they discriminated? Yes. Where their movements controlled? Less than palestinian's but, to a degree, yes. Where they killed? Yes. Where their communities destroyed? Yes. Where they costantly harassed? Yes. Where they treated like subhumans? Yes. Where oppressed by a discriminatory burocratic system? Yes. Where they segregated? Yes. But, ladies and gentlemen, they were allowed to work for the white people! I mean, if the US was really a bad place, they could have gathered them up, built a wall around them, starved them of water and electricity, and let them to die. But they didn't do that, so clearly it was all good. And you know what? It was more than good, it was the most moral nation in the world.
